About Me



Greetings!

Welcome to my project! I have been to a Hackathon before, but THIS is big scale! I am very excited to see what all other contenders create :)



Introduction

I'm Shalaka- and yes, this is a solo project! People consider me as a creative, competitive and curious individual.

How Finding the Google Hackathon Helped Me Make This

When I stumbled upon the Google Women Techmakers Hackathon, I saw it as the perfect opportunity to apply my skills to a cause that I truly care about: gender equity. The hackathon’s challenge to create an AI-powered solution aligned perfectly with my vision of using technology for social good. It gave me the inspiration and drive to build this project, combining my love for AI and my commitment to empowering women. The journey has been incredibly rewarding, and I’m proud of what I’ve created.

Personality Traits

I am creative, competitive, and curious. My creativity drives me to think outside the box, finding new and innovative solutions to problems. I thrive on competition, constantly pushing myself to improve and be the best version of myself. Curiosity is at the core of my work—I’m always learning, experimenting, and seeking new ways to grow, whether through coding, exploring new technologies, or tackling fresh challenges.

Thank you for visiting my page, and I hope this project can inspire change and spark important conversations!
